This paper discusses the implementation of a new neuron circuit that uses adaptive LIF neuron models to reduce power consumption in neural processing systems. The paper focuses on the analogies and differences between the proposed circuit and a first-order sigma-delta feedback loop. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.ET (Embedded Systems), cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
